The 2,500 tonnes of sugar offered tointervention in the Netherlands has been refused by theintervention board because of wrong packaging, a spokeswomanfor the Ministry of Agriculture said.    She said the sugar could be offered again to intervention.    EC producers have threatened to sell over 800,000 tonnes ofsugar to intervention stocks as a protest against EC exportlicensing policies.    Last month Dutch traders said the sugar on offer in theNetherlands was Belgian, but the ministry could not confirmthis. REUTER&#3;